ast November to explore options for improving redress in the housing market.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","133722 ; 133726","2018-04-19T14:35:38.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868508/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868508/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868508/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-03-21","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to ensure greater protection and improved redress for consumers where developers of new build homes fail to complete the development infrastructure and in the event that infrastructure utilities refuse to adopt that infrastructure.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","133728"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868509","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-28","<p>The Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency is a Government trading fund, and will continue to be so after the United Kingdom leaves the European Union. As a Government trading fund, the Agency will carry on recovering costs in the usual way.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-03-28T12:42:31.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868509/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868509/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868509/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-21","Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of the need for additional investment in the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","133729"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868510","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-29","<p>The Department does not hold this information as we do not collect data about un-adopted roads. A local highway authority may adopt a road if it has been built to the required standard. It will then become maintainable at the public’s expense. An authority will not, however, adopt a road that does not meet the required standard. Some developers do not seek adoption, and some residents will prefer to keep the road as private.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-03-29T10:51:19.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868510/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868510/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868510/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-03-21","Private Roads","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many new build developments have included roads which have not been adopted by local authorities due to not meeting minimum standards in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","133730"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868511","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-29","<p>The Government is committed to supporting innovation and improvement through the safe and secure use of data from the health and care system. NHS Digital is the national provider of high-quality information, data and IT systems for health and social care, with a statutory duty in the Health and Social Care Act 2012, to assure the quality of all the data it collects, publishes and makes available, under strict controls, to the research community. At present, a wide range of data is collected from the National Health Service to support a range of secondary uses including within the research community. Recognising the value and importance of this data, NHS Digital has made a number of commitments to the Life Sciences Industrial Strategy. In addition, NHS Digital has set out national standards and approaches for data and interoperability and sponsors the Professional Records Standards Body to define the standards needed for good care records which are the foundation of strong data for research. To support researchers understanding of the data access environment, NHS Digital is also rolling out a series of Roadshows for Researchers which will promote understanding of the types of data that are available for research and how to access this data.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-03-29T11:23:28.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868511/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868511/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868511/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-21","Medical Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that the UK is at the global forefront of collecting and using patient data to improve health and care outcomes.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","133731"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868512","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-26","<p>The current Cold Weather Payment service is supported by measurements of air temperature and wind chill is not taken into account.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-03-26T16:36:21.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868512/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868512/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868512/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-21","Cold Weather Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether wind chill factor is taken into account in the calculation of cold weather payments.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","133732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868513","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-26","<p>Bed availability and occupancy is rightly managed at a local level. Nationally, the National Health Service planned earlier than ever before to cope with winter this year when we know demand for beds increases. This was supported by an additional £337 million which included funding to make sure additional beds were made available to patients during heightened seasonal demand.</p><p> </p><p>Hospitals have a responsibility in ensuring that they are operating with the necessary beds available to support effective patient flow and safety.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-03-26T15:53:02.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868513/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868513/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868513/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-21","Hospital Beds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent assessment he has made of the adequacy of bed capacity in NHS hospitals.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","133733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868514","Department for International Development","false","2018-03-26","<p>We determine that President Htin Kyaw’s resignation will not have any impact on DFID’s operations in Burma.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-26T15:32:36.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868514/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868514/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868514/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-03-21","Burma: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the potential effect of the resignation of the Burmese President, Htin Kyaw, on her Department's programmes in Burma.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","133734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868515","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-29","<p>The UK has exported a number of items to Israel over the last three years, including body armour, equipment to deal with military improvised explosive devices, and components for targeting equipment, military communications, tanks and military support aircraft and vehicles. We do not collect data on the use of equipment after sale. UK arms exports are subject to export controls. All decisions to approve export licences to Israel are considered on a case-by-case basis against the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria (Consolidated Criteria). Decisions are based on the most up-to-date information and analysis available, including reports from our overseas network and military contacts. The Consolidated Criteria provide a thorough risk assessment framework and require us to consider the impact of providing equipment and its capabilities. We do not issue export licences where, for example, we assess there is a clear risk that the goods might be used for internal repression. We keep our approach to all countries under continual review.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-29T14:54:44.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868515/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868515/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868515/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-21","Occupied Territories","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether any UK-supplied military-related equipment has been used in Israeli police or military operations in the Occupied Palestinian Territories in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","133735"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868516","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-28","<p>In the past five years, 56 Egyptian military officers have been trained in the UK; seven in 2013-14; nine in 2014-15; eight in 2015-16; 16 in 2016-17; and 16 in 2017-18.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-03-28T15:27:29.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868516/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868516/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868516/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-21","Egypt: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the number of Egyptian military officers who have been trained in the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","133736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868517","Home Office","false","2018-04-03","<p>The Home Office does not comment on intelligence matters nor on matters which form part of ongoing investigations.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2018-04-03T15:44:34.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868517/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868517/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868517/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-21","Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what information the Government holds on with which groups Salman Abedi and his father, Ramadan Abedi, fought in Libya in 2011.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","133737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868518","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-29","<p>The Government is working closely with our European partners and with civil society on a Summit agenda for London that will help foster regional security, economic and political cooperation. The Summit Team have met LGBT activists from the region (organised by Stonewall) as part of our engagement with civil society on the Summit.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-03-29T16:44:57.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868518/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868518/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868518/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-21","Balkans: LGBT People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will include LGBT rights on the agenda of the forthcoming Western Balkans summit in London.","false","Biography information for Nick Herbert","Arundel and South Downs","Nick Herbert","133738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868519","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-03-26","<p>The Rural Payments Agency are required to demonstrate compliance with the EU rules by keeping our mapping up to date or run the risk of significant disallowance. Updates to our maps are based on the intelligence we receive from Ordnance Survey; aerial photography; inspection outcomes; and requests made by farmers. They have notified customers of all changes made to their land parcel information.</p><p>Key stakeholders have been engaged throughout the exercise to raise awareness, and the RPA has provided advice and guidance to support applicants for Basic Payment Scheme 2018 in making an accurate claim. This includes a dedicated helpline and page on rpa.gov.uk dedicated to mapping.</p><p>The RPA has established processes which take into account, on a case-by-case basis, any evidence or information submitted by farmers should any differences be found.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-03-26T17:17:59.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868519/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868519/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868519/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-21","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans the Government has to ensure that farmers are not penalised if they make a mistaken claim as a result of a mapping error caused by the re-mapping conducted by the Rural Payments Agency.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","133739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868520","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-03-26","<p>The Rural Payments Agency (RPA) have reviewed and updated over 2 million parcels to bring the information in line with EU requirements. As of 23 March the RPA had received and reviewed 527 forms to request changes to the updates and of these 48 forms required action to make corrections to the mapping updates.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-03-26T17:14:16.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868520/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868520/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868520/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-21","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of new maps produced this year by the Rural Payments Agency is being disputed by CAP claimants.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","133740"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868521","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-03-26","<p>The Rural Payments Agency (RPA) is required to demonstrate compliance with the EU rules by keeping our mapping up to date or run the risk of significant disallowance. Updates to our maps are based on the intelligence we receive from Ordnance Survey; aerial photography; inspection outcomes; and requests made by farmers.</p><p> </p><p>The RPA don’t capture information on what individual parcel boundary changes were the result of the exercise to update their mapping, in line with EU requirements, and what changes were the result of farmer changes to field management.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-03-26T17:17:42.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868521/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868521/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868521/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-21","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, in what proportion of farm holdings boundaries changed as a result of this year’s re-mapping by the Rural Payments Agency.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","133741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868522","Department for International Development","false","2018-03-26","<p>We recognise the immediate need to increase the provision of protection services in the Rohingya refugee camps. DFID is leading the way in supporting a range of organisations providing specialised help to survivors of sexual violence. We are supporting 25 women’s centres, which are providing safe space, psychosocial support and activities to women and girls. We are also funding case management for over 2,000 survivors of sexual and gender-based violence.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-26T15:33:03.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868522/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868522/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868522/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-03-21","Bangladesh: Rohingya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to protect Rohingya women and girls from sexual violence in refugee camps in Bangladesh .","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","133742"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868523","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-03","<p>The “applicable amount” for Jobseeker’s Allowance is set each year by the government after a review of the level of benefit that a claimant may receive. The rates for Jobseeker’s Allowance were originally based on the equivalent provisions for Income Support, which were in force in October 1996, when JSA replaced the element of that benefit for those who are unemployed, on low or no income or other financial means and are available and looking for work.</p><p> </p><p>The proposed benefit and pension rates for 2018/19 can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/proposed-benefit-and-pension-rates-2018-to-2019" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/proposed-benefit-and-pension-rates-2018-to-2019</a></p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-04-03T14:55:43.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868523/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868523/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868523/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-21","Jobseeker's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what formula is used to determine the figures for the JSA Applicable Amount as set out in regulations 83 and 84 (1) of Schedule 1 on Applicable Amount Part 1 Personal Allowances in the Jobseeker's Allowance Regulations 1996.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","133743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868524","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-26","<p>The Department does not hold information regarding assessment of patients’ ability to access records held on them by hospitals.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-03-26T15:01:23.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868524/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868524/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868524/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-21","Medical Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent assessment he has made of patients' ability to access records held on them by hospitals; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","133744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868525","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-29","<p>The Survey and Inspection transformation programme is a four-year change programme currently less than halfway through implementation. The changes to the Marine Office network estate laydown remain on schedule to complete in March 2019 and the new North East Examination Centre has already opened in South Shields.</p><p> </p><p>An assessment of the impact of the changes will be undertaken at an appropriate time after implementation has completed.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-03-29T10:55:01.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868525/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868525/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868525/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-03-21","Maritime and Coastguard Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of changes to the Maritime and Coastguard Agency’s national network of marine offices on (a) vessel surveyor support and (b) seafarer examination and certification services.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","133745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868526","Treasury","false","2018-03-26","<p>Departments publish quarterly details of Ministers’ meetings with external organisations on GOV.UK. These can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p><p> </p><p>As well as ministerial meetings, departmental officials meet external organisations on a regular and ongoing basis.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-03-26T16:05:03.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868526/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868526/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868526/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-21","Treasury: Cambridge Analytica and SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has met representatives of (a) SCL Group, (b) Strategic Communication Laboratories and (c) Cambridge Analytica; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","133746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868527","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-27","<p>The Department is now working to implement the MH Upper Tribunal judgment, which changes how overwhelming psychological distress should be considered in assessing a person’s ability to plan and follow a journey under Mobility Activity 1 of Personal Independence Payment (PIP). We are currently engaging with a range of stakeholder on changes to Departmental guidance. We are committed to taking this work forward at pace over the coming months, and will publish new guidance in due course.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","133749","2018-03-27T13:40:33.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868527/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868527/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868527/answer","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868527/answer/previousversion/49869","Biography information for Sarah Newton","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-21","Personal Independence Payment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he expects new guidelines on mental illness and personal independence payments (PIP) to be issued to PIP assessors.","false","Biography information for Dr Philippa Whitford","Central Ayrshire","Dr Philippa Whitford","133747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868528","Treasury","false","2018-03-26","<p>No contracts have been held with those companies.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-03-26T16:03:34.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868528/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868528/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868528/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-21","Treasury: Cambridge Analytica and SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether (a) his Department and (b) his Department's agencies and public bodies have held contracts with (i) SCL group, (ii) Strategic Communication Laboratories and (iii) Cambridge Analytica.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","133748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868529","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-27","<p>The Department is now working to implement the MH Upper Tribunal judgment, which changes how overwhelming psychological distress should be considered in assessing a person’s ability to plan and follow a journey under Mobility Activity 1 of Personal Independence Payment (PIP). We are currently engaging with a range of stakeholder on changes to Departmental guidance. We are committed to taking this work forward at pace over the coming months, and will publish new guidance in due course.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","133747","2018-03-27T13:40:33.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868529/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868529/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868529/answer","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868529/answer/previousversion/49872","Biography information for Sarah Newton","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-21","Personal Independence Payment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what progress has her Department has made on writing new guidelines for personal independence payments that take account of the effect of mental health conditions on an person's mobility.","false","Biography information for Dr Philippa Whitford","Central Ayrshire","Dr Philippa Whitford","133749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868530","Department for International Trade","false","2018-03-28","<p>My Rt Hon. Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade has not met representatives of SCL Group or Cambridge Analytica.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-03-28T15:28:42.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868530/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868530/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868530/answer","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868530/answer/previousversion/49863","Biography information for Greg Hands","202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-03-21","Department for International Trade: Cambridge Analytica and SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether he has met representatives of (a) SCL Group and (b) Cambridge Analytica.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","133750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868531","Department for International Trade","false","2018-03-27","<p>The Department for International Trade does not hold any contracts with SCL Group and Cambridge Analytica.</p><p>The Department for International Trade does not currently have any agencies and public bodies.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-03-27T12:07:56.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868531/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868531/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868531/answer","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868531/answer/previousversion/49864","Biography information for Greg Hands","202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-03-21","Department for International Trade: Cambridge Analytica and SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether (a) his Department and (b) his Department's agencies and public bodies have held contracts with (i) SCL Group and (ii) Cambridge Analytica.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","133751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868532","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-27","<p>Personal Independence Payment (PIP) is not awarded on the basis of an individual’s diagnosis. It is a needs based assessment which looks at how an individual’s condition(s) affects their ability to do everyday tasks.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-03-27T13:49:13.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868532/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868532/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868532/answer","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868532/answer/previousversion/49841","Biography information for Sarah Newton","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-21","Personal Independence Payment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, which mental health conditions will be included in the new Personal Independence Payment guidelines.","false","Biography information for Dr Philippa Whitford","Central Ayrshire","Dr Philippa Whitford","133752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868533","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-03-26","<p>Departments publish quarterly details of Ministers’ meetings with external organisations on GOV.UK. These can be found at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-environment-food-rural-affairs&amp;publication_type=transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-environment-food-rural-affairs&amp;publication_type=transparency-data</a></p><p> </p><p>As well as ministerial meetings, departmental officials meet external organisations on a regular and ongoing basis.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-03-26T17:20:05.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868533/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868533/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868533/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-21","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Cambridge Analytica and SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether his Department has met representatives of (a) SCL Group, (b) Strategic Communication Laboratories and (c) Cambridge Analytica; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","133753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868534","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-27","<p>Health Care Professionals (HCPs) undertaking PIP assessments must have at least 2 years post full registration experience (this refers to either UK registration or equivalent overseas registration for non-UK HPs) or less than 2 years post full registration experience by individual, prior, written agreement with the Department. Requests by providers to employ Health Professionals with less than 2 years post full registration experience is rare and exceptional.</p><p> </p><p>All HCPs receive training on how to identify the impact of mental health conditions on claimants. This is followed by on-going professional training and support which continues for the duration of their employment in the role.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, Mental Health Champions support HCPs by providing additional expertise about mental health, cognitive, developmental and learning disabilities and can be referred to at any time during the assessment process.</p><p> </p><p>HCPs make every attempt to obtain the best evidence available to assist them in undertaking the assessment. This includes accessing evidence from Community Mental Health Teams, psychologists, psychiatrists and other medical professionals. Health Assessment Providers frequently engage with medical experts, charities and relevant stakeholders to strengthen review and update training programmes for all their assessment staff.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-03-27T13:59:50.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868534/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868534/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868534/answer","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868534/answer/previousversion/49844","Biography information for Sarah Newton","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-21","Personal Independence Payment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what training personal independence payment assessors receive on mental illness and the disabilities that result from them.","false","Biography information for Dr Philippa Whitford","Central Ayrshire","Dr Philippa Whitford","133754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868535","Department for Education","false","2018-03-26","<p>This information is already in the public domain. The Department publishes the amount spent by schools on supply teaching staff and agency supply teaching staff (as well as costs and receipts from supply teacher insurance) annually for:</p><p>Local authority maintained schools on the Department’s School and College Performance website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/school-performance-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/school-performance-tables</a> available for 2010-11 to 2016-17; and</p><p>Academies in the department’s Statistical First Release ‘Income and expenditure in academies in England’: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-local-authority-school-finance-data#academy-spending" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-local-authority-school-finance-data#academy-spending</a> available since 2011/12, when they were first collected in this format, up to 2015/16. Data for 2016/17 will published in the summer of 2018.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","133756","2018-03-26T16:13:54.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868535/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868535/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868535/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-21","Supply Teachers: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate his Department has made of the total spending by (a) maintained schools and (b) academies on supply teachers in each of the last five financial years.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","133755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868536","Department for Education","false","2018-03-26","<p>This information is already in the public domain. The Department publishes the amount spent by schools on supply teaching staff and agency supply teaching staff (as well as costs and receipts from supply teacher insurance) annually for:</p><p>Local authority maintained schools on the Department’s School and College Performance website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/school-performance-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/school-performance-tables</a> available for 2010-11 to 2016-17; and</p><p>Academies in the department’s Statistical First Release ‘Income and expenditure in academies in England’: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-local-authority-school-finance-data#academy-spending" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-local-authority-school-finance-data#academy-spending</a> available since 2011/12, when they were first collected in this format, up to 2015/16. Data for 2016/17 will published in the summer of 2018.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","133755","2018-03-26T16:13:54.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868536/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868536/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868536/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-21","Schools: Employment Agencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate his Department has made of the total amount spent by (a) maintained schools and (b) academies on agency supply staff in each of the last five financial years.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","133756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868537","Department for International Development","false","2018-03-26","<p>Given the severe humanitarian impact that heavy rains and cyclones could have on Rohingya refugees, we have been urging the Government of Bangladesh and partners to prepare for the forthcoming heavy rains. The Foreign Secretary and the Secretary of State for International Development wrote to Bangladesh’s Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina on 20 March, calling to attention the need to reduce the density of shelters in the camps, and provide options for people to move to land that is at a lower risk of flooding.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-26T15:31:49.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868537/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868537/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868537/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-03-21","Bangladesh: Rohingya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent discussions she has had with her Bangladeshi counterpart on the emergency relocation of Rohingya refugees living in shelters most at risk from monsoon rains and cyclones; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","133757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868538","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-28","<p>The General Medical Council (GMC) is the independent regulator of medical doctors in the United Kingdom, and is not responsible for assessing or enforcing measures put in place by National Health Service trusts.</p><p> </p><p>All UK registered doctors are expected to meet the professional standards set out in the GMC’s Good Medical Practice. To maintain their licence to practise, a doctor must demonstrate, through the revalidation process, that they work in line with the principles and values set out in this guidance.</p><p> </p><p>If an allegation is made about a doctor that their fitness to practise is impaired, the GMC has a duty to investigate and take action to safeguard the health and well-being of the public. In the most serious cases fitness to practise proceedings can result in doctors being removed from the medical register.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-03-28T12:48:48.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868538/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868538/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868538/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-21","Patients: Sexual Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what role the General Medical Council plays in (a) assessing and (b) enforcing safeguarding measures put in place by NHS trusts after patients have made serious allegations of sexual assault.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","133758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868539","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-26","<p>Our Industrial Strategy aims to support entrepreneurs of all ages across the UK to ensure they can access the finance and wider support to grow and have the right conditions for companies to invest long-term.</p><p>The British Business Bank (BBB), through its Start Up Loans programme has lent over £400m to more than 54,000 entrepreneurs (at end of February 2018). Over 24,000 loans at a value of over £160m has been lent to individuals under the age of 30.</p><p>The Government also provides support to start-up businesses across England through GOV.UK and the Business Support Helpline. During financial year 2017/18, the Business Support Helpline provided support to 2,359 people under the age of 25.</p><p>In addition, the Government has supported and invested in the creation of a network of 38 Growth Hubs (one in each Local Enterprise Partnership area), helping simplify the business support landscape, providing joined up access to the full range of local and national support programmes (public and private).</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-03-26T15:45:59.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868539/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868539/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868539/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-03-21","New Businesses: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps his Department it taking to support young entrepreneurs.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","133759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868540","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-26","<p>The Government intends to publish both the submissions to the review and a list of who responded by the end of April.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-03-26T15:45:42.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868540/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868540/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868540/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-03-21","Modern Working Practices Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 23 February 2018 to Question 128539, what progress his Department is making on redacting personal information from the submissions to the Taylor Review of modern working practices; and what the timetable is for publishing copies of the written evidence submitted to that review on the Gov.uk website.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","133760"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868541","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-26","<p>The Mental Health Support Teams will include additional trained staff and will operate between schools, colleges and specialist services.</p><p> </p><p>The teams will receive supervision from National Health Service mental health staff and we will test a range of models to understand how best the teams work with other relevant professionals, such as educational psychologists, school nurses, counsellors and voluntary and community sector organisations. We will announce further details around how the teams will be trained and work in due course.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-03-26T14:54:22.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868541/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868541/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868541/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-21","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, in regard to the Mental Health Support Teams whose introduction is proposed in the Green Paper for Transforming Children and Young People’s Mental Health, who will (a) be included in Mental Health Support Teams proposed in the Green Paper for Transforming Children and Young People's Mental Health and (b) train and supervise those staff.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","133761"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868542","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-26","<p>The Department does not hold this information. Information provided by Health Education England on the number of training places that, following recruitment, remained unfilled in the fourth year of child and adolescent psychiatry single specialty training in each year since 2013, in the North West and in England, is shown in the table below:</p><p> </p><p>Unfilled ST4 Child and Adolescent Psychiatry posts through recruitment</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>North West</p></td><td><p>England</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>34</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>28</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p>National level data for the years prior to 2013 are not held centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-03-26T14:59:53.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868542/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868542/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868542/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-21","Psychiatry: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many training places for child and adolescent psychiatry were unfilled in each year since 2010 in (a) the North West and (b) England.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","133762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868543","Home Office","false","2018-03-26","<p>The appointment of a Chief Executive is a matter for the Gangmasters and Labour Abuse Authority, subject to the consent of the Home Secretary. The GLAA is expected to make an announcement shortly.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-03-26T13:49:00.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868543/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868543/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868543/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-21","Gangmasters and Labour Abuse Authority","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she has taken to identify a new Chief Executive to oversee the operations of the Gangmasters and Labour Abuse Authority; when an appointment to that role will be made; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","133763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868544","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-26","<p>The Government has put in place a range of grant schemes to support the installation of charging infrastructure, on-street, off-street and at workplaces, that are available in any urban or rural areas UK-wide. In addition, under the Government’s Go Ultra Low City Scheme £22.9m has been allocated to support the installation of infrastructure currently being procured and installed in several UK cities and wider surrounding rural areas. At the Autumn Budget in 2017, the Chancellor announced a new £400m electric vehicle Charging Infrastructure Investment Fund. This funding could include supporting chargepoints in both rural and urban areas, and more detail on how the Fund will be administered will be published in due course. We are also taking powers through the Automated and Electric Vehicle Bill to ensure the roll-out of electric vehicle infrastructure at key locations such as motorway service areas and large fuel stations.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-03-26T15:04:01.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868544/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868544/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868544/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-03-21","Electric Vehicles: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to increase the (a) number and (b) distribution of charging points for electric cars in rural areas.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","133764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868545","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-26","<p>The Autumn budget provided the National Health Service with an additional £337 million of winter funding. Of this, up to £18 million was allocated for mental health services, such as providing additional liaison mental health staff to relieve pressure on accident and emergency units by identifying patients in need of specialist treatment and referring them to more appropriate care more quickly.</p><p> </p><p>Specific funding for mental health services was not separately identified as part of winter funding for previous years, however these services will have benefitted from the provision of additional resources to support increased demand over the winter period.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-03-26T14:51:21.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868545/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868545/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868545/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-21","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what proportion of the additional funding for winter pressures was spent on mental health services in each year since 2013.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","133765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868546","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-26","<p>Sport England, the government arms' length body with responsibility for supporting grassroots sport, has a number of investment funds which local sports clubs can apply to, including their Small Grants fund and the Community Asset Fund.</p><p> </p><p>Detailed information, including prospectuses and guidance on how to apply, can be found on Sport England’s website. Sport England's Club Matters web page also contains a section on ‘Club Management’ which covers topics including Community Amateur Sports Clubs (CASC), club structures and managing risk.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, Sport England revised and relaunched its commercial framework in June 2017. The framework will help organisations to reduce the levels of public funding they are reliant on through finding alternative sources of private investment.</p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-03-26T14:12:06.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868546/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868546/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868546/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-21","Sports: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department is taking to help local sports clubs access funding.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","133766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868547","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-26","<p>The Child Maintenance Service uses annually updated income information provided by HMRC to assess maintenance liabilities. The aim is that a liability, once created, stays in force for a year excepting significant income changes of 25% or more. This provides certainty and stability for both parents to allow them to budget effectively to the benefit of their children; and removes the need for paying parents to keep the Service updated of every change to their income. We continue to monitor the impact of the reformed child maintenance scheme.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-03-26T16:41:13.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868547/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868547/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868547/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-21","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, for what reasons the Child Maintenance Service only reviews of a person's payments when their income changes by 25% or more; and what assessment has she made of the effect of that policy on people whose decrease in salary does not meet the 25% threshold.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","133767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868548","Women and Equalities","false","2018-04-03","<p>The Chancellor announced a £5 million fund in the Budget in March 2017 to help celebrate the centenary of women’s suffrage. My officials at the GEO have set up a number of projects to mark this important anniversary in British democracy.</p><p>The largest proportion of the fund has been allocated to the Women’s Suffrage Centenary Grant Scheme. The total value of the contract is £1.5m (incl. VAT). Of that figure, 7% (£108,000) is allocated to Ecorys to administer the Centenary Grant Scheme, and 93% (£1,392,000) is allocated to two funding streams: the small grants stream has a ceiling of £2,000 to support small local celebratory events. The larger grants stream covers projects from £2,000 to £125,000 that will increase young people’s understanding of and engagement with democracy; and encourage women to participate in public life.</p><p>The contract has been published on the government contracts finder page and can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Notice/c545f59a-95c2-435e-b9db-959121563339" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Notice/c545f59a-95c2-435e-b9db-959121563339</a></p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-04-03T15:50:14.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868548/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868548/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868548/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-03-21","Females: Voting Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what the value of the contract is for Ecorys to administer the Women's Vote Centenary Grant Scheme.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","133768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868549","Home Office","false","2018-03-28","<p>On 19 December 2017 the Minister responsible for Hate Crime Baroness Williams attended a seminar on online hate that was arranged by the Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government. The seminar included representatives from Facebook, Google, Microsoft and Twitter.</p><p>Officials will continue to engage with social media companies about what more they can do to tackle online hate crime.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-03-28T16:26:44.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868549/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868549/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868549/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-21","Hate Crime: Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent meetings her Department has had with social media companies on tackling online hate crime.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","133769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868550","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-28","<p>Ministers and officials from across Government have carried out extensive engagement to hear a range of views on our EU exit. As such, we work with women involved in businesses, think tanks, academia, voluntary organisations and many other groups, listening to their perspectives on our future partnership with the EU and other matters. This is in addition to the engagement we have with groups focused on women’s rights and equalities.</p><p> </p>","Fareham","Suella Fernandes",,"2018-03-28T10:50:52.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868550/answer","Biography information for Suella Braverman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868550/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868550/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-03-21","Females: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that women’s views are represented in negotiations to leave the EU.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","133770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868551","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-26","<p>The use of offensive lethal force overseas is controlled by robust Rules of Engagement and is ordinarily confined to armed conflicts in which the UK is openly involved. However, and as the Government has stated previously, if the UK is subject to an armed attack or the imminent threat of an armed attack, it reserves the right to take action first and inform Parliament after the event. Any decision to use lethal force outside of an armed conflict would be conducted on a case by case basis but always cognisant of the international law principles of necessity and proportionality.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-03-26T15:33:14.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868551/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868551/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868551/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-21","Law of War","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the use of lethal force is confined to (a) armed conflicts in which the UK is openly involved and (b) exceptional circumstances in which there is an imminent threat to the UK.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","133771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868552","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-26","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for Sheffield South East (Mr Clive Betts) in response to Question 128425 on 22 February 2018.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-03-26T15:32:35.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868552/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868552/answer","Hansard Extract Thursday 22 February 2018 HOC 128435.docx","128425 - WQnA extract on MOD Law of War","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868552/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-21","Law of War","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will publish the UK’s (a) legal framework and (b) guidance on its use of lethal force.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","133772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868553","Women and Equalities","false","2018-04-03","<p>The Government takes the issue of workplace discrimination very seriously.</p><p>Following the inquiry into high heels and workplace dress codes, the House of Commons Petitions Committee and Women and Equalities Select Committee recommended that the Government Equalities Office (GEO) produce guidance on dress codes. The GEO has worked with the Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service (Acas), the Health and Safety Executive (HSE) and the Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) to prepare guidance for employers and employees to help them understand how discrimination law and health and safety law apply to workplace dress codes.</p><p>The purpose of the GEO dress code guidance is to raise awareness of existing statutory protections, so employers can avoid discriminatory policies and practices on dress codes. We will publish this guidance shortly.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-04-03T15:39:22.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868553/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868553/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868553/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-03-21","Employment: Clothing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, whether the government has plans to publish guidance on dress codes that state that (a) policy and (b) practice by employers must be non-discriminatory.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","133773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868554","Women and Equalities","false","2018-04-03","<p>In 2017, the government introduced ground-breaking regulations requiring large employers, in both the public and private sector, to publish their gender pay gaps annually. The transparency generated by these regulations will motivate employers to identify barriers to women’s progression in the workplace, and to take action to address them.</p><p>This builds on previous success in using transparency to drive change, including our support for the Hampton-Alexander Review to achieve 33% women on boards, and 33% women in Executive Committees and positions reporting directly to the Executive Committee in the FTSE 350 by 2020.</p><p>In October 2017 we also published the Race Disparity Audit to give an unprecedented insight into how people from different ethnic backgrounds are treated in society, including their access to healthcare, education, employment and in the criminal justice system.</p><p>These actions are underpinned by legislation to safeguard rights in the workplace. The Equality Act 2010 makes it unlawful to discriminate against someone because of pregnancy or maternity. The Equality and Human Rights Commission and Acas provide advice and guidance to employees who feel they have experienced discrimination. We also fund the Equality Advisory and Support Service, a free advice helpline open to anyone in England, Scotland and Wales who feels that they may have been the victim of unlawful discrimination.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-04-03T15:59:05.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868554/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868554/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868554/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-03-21","Equal Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what steps the Government is taking to tackle discrimination in the workplace to help reduce the gender pay gap.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","133774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868555","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","true","2018-03-29","<p>In 2016 Tourism accounted for £66bn GVA, which was <del class="ministerial">14.2%</del> <ins class="ministerial">3.8%</ins>of the total UK GVA.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-03-29T14:41:53.66Z","2018-05-14T16:37:18.167Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868555/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868555/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868555/answer","Northampton North","Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868555/answer/previousversion/50829","Biography information for Michael Ellis","10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-21","Tourism: National Income","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of gross domestic product tourism accounts for.","false","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","133775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868556","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-27","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for Worsley and Eccles South (Barbara Keeley) on 26 February 2018 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=128962" target="_blank">128962</a>.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-03-27T14:50:52.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868556/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868556/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868556/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-21","Social Services: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent estimate he has made of sleep-in back liability for providers in Bedfordshire.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","133776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868557","Women and Equalities","false","2018-04-03","<p>The Government has commissioned an evidence review to identify the barriers that limit women’s participation in national government. The aim is to provide political parties with a range of solutions to draw on.</p><p>We are also developing a programme to inspire young women, from all backgrounds, to be leaders in their communities, and develop the skills and aspiration for careers in public life, at all levels of governance. We will share more details in due course.</p><p>Additionally, the Centenary Grant Scheme will award funding to projects to encourage women to participate in public life. We will prioritise projects that are aimed at women and/or young people who are underrepresented such as people from lower socio-economic groups, people who are BAME, LGBT and/or living with a disability.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-04-03T12:25:32.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868557/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868557/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868557/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-03-21","Elections: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what steps the Government is taking to encourage more women from diverse backgrounds to enter elected politics.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","133777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868558","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-29","<p>In November 2015, the Government announced the £40 million Discover England Fund (DEF), an unprecedented opportunity for investment in improving English tourism product.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>We have been working with VisitEngland to encourage more domestic visitors to explore the country and discover all there is to see and experience on their doorstep this spring. For example, the annual celebration of English tourism, English Tourism Week has just concluded. Further details can be found here: <a href="https://www.visitbritain.org/english-tourism-week" target="_blank">https://www.visitbritain.org/english-tourism-week</a>.</p><p> </p><p>VisitEngland have various projects aimed at promoting domestic tourism and building our domestic product, such a rail ‘final mile’ campaign and developing food hubs across the country. VisitEngland also worked with VisitScotland and Visit Wales to launch a major domestic campaign for summer 2017, focussed on encouraging young people to holiday at home.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-03-29T14:45:24.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868558/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868558/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868558/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-21","Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to promote domestic tourism in England.","false","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","133778"
