"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868574","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-26","<p>This data is not available. However, cystic fibrosis is estimated to affect about 7,700 people in England (1 in 2,500 live births).</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-03-26T15:25:35.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868574/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868574/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/868574/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-21","Cystic Fibrosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many people suffer from cystic fibrosis in (a) Newcastle, (b) the north east of England and (c) England.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","133793"
