"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867424","Treasury","false","2018-03-28","<p>HM Revenue and Customs does not hold information on VAT revenues that can be broken down to the requested level of detail.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-03-28T10:20:20.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867424/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867424/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867424/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-20","Aviation: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much revenue was raised from VAT on flight training in the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for John Stevenson","Carlisle","John Stevenson","133399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867425","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-26","<p>Openreach does not have direct relationships with residential consumers. Consumer complaints should, in the first instance, be made to the communications company that provides the retail services and they will take them up with Openreach where necessary. If a customer is still unhappy after they have made a complaint to their provider, they can ask CICAS or the Ombudsman Services to investigate.</p><p> </p><p>Ofcom does not handle individual complaints but it monitors and analyses complaints and, where it sees evidence of recurring harm, it can take action. This process enables Ofcom to track the types of issue that affect consumers most and any providers that appear to be responsible for causing harm.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, Ofcom sets Openreach quality of service standards, which it is raising following its review of the Wholesale Local Access (WLA) market. Ofcom will monitor Openreach’s performance against these standards closely and step in if these are not met.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-26T14:56:42.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867425/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867425/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867425/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-20","Openreach: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether (a) Ofcom and (b) the Ombudsman has the power to investigate complaints in respect of Openreach.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","133400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867426","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-28","<p>The Department’s “British Road Safety Statement” published in December 2015 sets out the Government’s commitment to actions that do support the UN Decade for Road Safety. This includes measures to improve safety and reduce deaths for vulnerable road users such as cyclists, pedestrians and motorcyclists. It also includes enhancing road infrastructure and encouraging improved learning and road behaviour. There are also actions on tackling mobile phone use whilst driving.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-03-28T12:00:50.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867426/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867426/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867426/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-03-20","Roads: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to support the UN Decade of Action for Road Safety.","false","Biography information for Martin Whitfield","East Lothian","Martin Whitfield","133401"
