"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867429","Treasury","false","2018-03-26","<p>We are replacing childcare vouchers with Tax-Free Childcare, which will provide support to nearly 1 million more families than currently use childcare vouchers. Childcare vouchers will remain open to new entrants for a further 6 months, and close to new entrants in October.</p><p> </p><p>Tax-Free Childcare is now fully rolled out, and we will keep it under review to ensure it’s delivering the support needed for working families.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-03-26T13:13:37.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867429/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867429/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867429/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-20","Child Care Vouchers","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the oral answer of the Secretary of State for Education to the hon. Member for Ashton-under-Lyne of 19 March 2018, Official Report, column 17, on childcare vouchers, what transitional considerations the Government will assess; and what steps it is taking to assess them.","false","Biography information for Stephanie Peacock","Barnsley East","Stephanie Peacock","133404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867430","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-26","<p>The National Security Council has agreed the high-level findings of the National Security Capability Review. Ministers have agreed that we should finalise the National Security Capability Review with a view to publishing the conclusions in spring.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2018-03-26T15:38:27.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867430/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867430/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867430/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-20","National Security Capability Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the timetable is for the publication of the National Security Capability Review.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","133405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867431","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-28","<p>The assessment criteria for Personal Independence Payment (PIP) have been developed to take into account the overall impact of a claimant’s physical or mental health condition or impairment on their functional ability, rather than focusing on a particular diagnosis. The inclusion in the assessment of activities around communicating, engaging with others, and planning and following journeys assists with assessing the impact of conditions affecting mental, intellectual, cognitive and developmental functions.</p><p> </p><p>66% of PIP recipients with mental health conditions get the enhanced rate daily living component, compared with 22% who received the highest DLA care component. And 31% of PIP recipients with mental health conditions get the enhanced rate mobility rate, compared with just 10% of DLA recipients.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-03-28T14:22:18.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867431/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867431/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867431/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-20","Personal Independence Payment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if she will make an assessment of the adequacy of the criteria for assessments for personal independence payments for people with mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Bottomley","Worthing West","Sir Peter Bottomley","133406"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867432","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-27","<p>We intend to be in a position to share headline conclusions from the Modernising Defence Programme in time for the NATO Summit in July.</p>","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson",,"2018-03-27T15:11:08.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867432/answer","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867432/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867432/answer","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867432/answer/previousversion/49800","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-20","Defence: Modernisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the timetable is for the publication of the Defence Modernisation Programme.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","133407"
